    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available now is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46). At its heart lies the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS, delivering a linear power band up to a 7,900 RPM redline. This example is equipped with the Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission for maximum tactile engagement. The chassis is mechanically sound, benefiting from proactive subframe reinforcement and a recently overhauled cooling system. Power is managed via the M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring precise torque distribution. While the exterior and interior show minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the suspension geometry remains tight and the engine pull is vigorous. This is a visceral, analog machine optimized for performance enthusiasts.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
